reviews.review: Rotten Tomatoes critics have it right, 55%. I was one eyelash away from falling asleep during the first hour. What was with the close ups of Daisy Ridley every 50 seconds? The first entry way back in a Galaxy far far away, Star Wars, was ground breaking in so many ways. Empire Strikes Back was a terrific, if not better, second act with Return of the Jedi an acceptable and satisfying conclusion. Since then, with perhaps the exception of Star Wars: The Last Jedi, the franchise has been far far inferior...

Enjoyable and fun, good to see all of the Star wars characters

The movie's story line was comically bad with fan fiction level of writing. The ending scene had multiple people in the audience with me laughing because of how ridiculous it was; not to mention the gentleman behind me snoring at a 3 o'clock showing. The special effects; however, are second to none. This movie was saved by the excellent work by the women and men in the special effects department. If you're looking for a visually stunning movie, look no further than ROS but don't expect to understand anything unless you have extensive knowledge of the Star Wars expanded universe.
Movie was fantastic!! Absolutely loved it, and a good finish for the series!

Overall narrative was good and scenes were pretty good, but in the same token it felt rushed and underdeveloped. Almost seemed it needed another hour, hour and a half to fully tell the story. Actors I believe did the best job they could under the circumstances.
Exactly what you want in a Star Wars film. Took me back to the feeling I had when I first watched the Original Trilogy.
Great movie one of the best

I enjoyed the story line, like the Star Wars episode before, the special effects are the best I've ever seen in movies. The twist on the story is a surprise and one that I did not see coming, I've put in my own guess before I watched it, and my guess was off, two thumbs up !

It has some some cheesy parts, but I still really enjoyed the movie. It left me excited to see where they take Star Wars next.
